sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor C as Customer
    participant APP as Customer App
    participant API as Cashback Redeem Service
    participant DB as MySQL
    participant LEDGER as Cashback Ledger
    participant PAY as Payment Flow
    participant GW as Payment Gateway

    C->>APP: At checkout sign in with phone
    APP->>API: GET cashback balance
    API->>DB: SELECT enrollment and balances
    DB-->>API: Available and pending amounts
    API-->>APP: Balance
    APP-->>C: Show balance and offer to apply
    C->>APP: Apply amount Y up to available

    APP->>API: POST cashback apply on payment

    API->>DB: BEGIN
    Note over API: Atomic redemption with FIFO partial drain across lots

    API->>DB: SELECT FOR UPDATE active matured lots ordered by available at then earned at then id
    DB-->>API: Locked active lots

    API->>API: Assert sum of remaining is at least Y or rollback as insufficient balance

    API->>DB: INSERT cashback redemption row with status pending and amount Y
    DB-->>API: Redemption id

    loop For each lot until Y is drained
        API->>API: Take is the lesser of lot remaining and Y left
        API->>DB: INSERT redemption consumption row with amount taken
        API->>DB: UPDATE lot consumed amount and flip status to fully consumed if drained
        API->>API: Subtract taken from Y left
    end

    API->>DB: UPDATE balances - subtract Y from available and add Y to lifetime redeemed
    API->>LEDGER: INSERT redeem event with balances and ids
    API->>DB: COMMIT

    API->>PAY: Apply discount to payment
    PAY->>PAY: Payable total is order total minus Y
    API-->>APP: Return redemption id and payable total
    APP-->>C: Show new total

    APP->>GW: Charge payable total

    alt Gateway success
        GW-->>APP: Paid
        APP->>API: POST cashback redemption confirm
        API->>DB: UPDATE redemption status to completed
        Note over API: Lots already debited at apply time so nothing more to do here
    else Gateway decline or abandoned
        GW-->>APP: Failed
        APP->>API: POST cashback redemption void
        API->>DB: BEGIN
        API->>DB: UPDATE redemption status to voided with reason
        loop For each consumption row of this redemption
            API->>DB: UPDATE lot - subtract amount and restore status to active if needed
        end
        API->>DB: UPDATE balances - add Y back to available and subtract Y from lifetime redeemed
        API->>LEDGER: INSERT void redemption event
        API->>DB: COMMIT
    end
